[SN]TITLE[SN]
Pensioner dies after Cork city house fire

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 78-year-old man has died following a fire at a house in the Ballinlough area of Cork city.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The fire broke out at a property where the man lived on Silverdale Road.
Cork Fire Brigade units received an emergency call at 13:30 local time.
A fire brigade spokesman said the fire was on the ground floor of the house and was brought under control in minutes.
